 sich in Denkfiguren, Rhetoriken, Symboliken und Handlungsweisen niederschlagen. Mit Beiträgen u.a. von Claus Leggewie und Susanne Schröter.  aWhat makes radical world views so attractive? And how can the revival of extremism be explained from the perspective of cultural and social studies? If major narratives were supposed to be found on the dump of history, they have lately found their way back into the discourse with the return of fundamentalism. The contributions in this book introduce mental figures and forms of rhetoric, symbolism and forms of behavior contained in various major narratives of extremes, and they discuss how the Western world embeds them in its own tale.  afunded by OGeSoMo  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aRadicalism. 0aReligious fundamentalism. 0aTerrorism. 4aFundamentalismus. 4aGewalt. 4aIslam. 4aIslamismus. 4aKrieg Gegen den Terror. 4aPolitik. 4aPolitikwissenschaft. 4aPolitische Ideologien. 4aPopulismus. 4aRechtsextremismus. 4aRechtsradikalismus. 4aTerrorismus. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Ideologies / General.2bisacsh  aFundamentalism.  aIslam.  aIslamism.  aPolitical Ideologies.  aPolitical Science.  aPolitics.  aPopulism.  aRight-wing Extremism.  aRight-wing Radicalism.  aTerrorism.  aViolence.  aWar on Terror.1 aDiehl, Paula, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEl-Mafaalani, Aladin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFlender, Armin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFlender, Armin, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHartleb, Florian, eco